prompts.prompt:
Act as a senior software engineer performing a code review. Analyze the following code for: 1) bugs and edge cases, 2) performance issues, 3) security vulnerabilities, 4) readability improvements, 5) adherence to best practices. Provide specific line-by-line feedback with suggested fixes.

Code:
{paste code here}

I'm encountering a bug. Help me debug it systematically:

Expected behavior: {what should happen}
Actual behavior: {what actually happens}
Steps to reproduce: {steps}
Environment: {language, framework, OS}
Error message: {paste error}

Walk me through the most likely causes from most to least probable, and suggest diagnostic steps for each.

Review this API design for RESTful best practices, consistency, security, and developer experience. Suggest improvements for naming conventions, error handling, pagination, versioning, and authentication.

API spec:
{paste your API endpoints/schema}

Generate comprehensive test cases for the following function/feature:

{paste function or describe feature}

Include: unit tests, edge cases, boundary values, error cases, integration test scenarios. Use {testing framework} syntax. Aim for >90% coverage.

Refactor this code to improve readability, maintainability, and performance while preserving exact behavior. Apply SOLID principles where applicable. Show the refactored version with comments explaining each change.

Code:
{paste code}

Write a {number}-email sequence for: {purpose, e.g., onboarding, sales, re-engagement}.

Product/Service: {describe}
Target audience: {describe}
Goal: {desired action}

For each email, provide: subject line, preview text, body copy, and CTA. Include send timing recommendations.

Write clear technical documentation for:

{paste code/API/feature description}

Include: Overview, Prerequisites, Installation/Setup, Usage Examples (beginner and advanced), API Reference (if applicable), Troubleshooting, and FAQ. Write for developers who are new to this tool.

Write a compelling product description for:

Product: {name}
Features: {list features}
Target customer: {describe}
Price point: {price}

Provide: headline, subheadline, 3 benefit-focused paragraphs, feature bullet points, social proof section template, and CTA. Optimize for conversion.

Write the following for my product/service: {describe}

1. AIDA (Attention, Interest, Desire, Action) copy
2. PAS (Problem, Agitate, Solution) copy
3. BAB (Before, After, Bridge) copy
4. 4Ps (Promise, Picture, Proof, Push) copy

Keep each under 150 words. Target audience: {describe}

Perform a competitor analysis for my business:

My business: {describe}
Competitors: {list 3-5}

Analyze for each: value proposition, pricing strategy, target audience, strengths, weaknesses, marketing channels, and unique differentiators. Create a comparison matrix and identify gaps I can exploit.

Fill out a complete Business Model Canvas for:

Business idea: {describe}

Provide detailed entries for all 9 blocks: Key Partners, Key Activities, Key Resources, Value Propositions, Customer Relationships, Channels, Customer Segments, Cost Structure, Revenue Streams. Include specific examples, not generic statements.

Write complete landing page copy for:

Product: {name}
Target user: {describe}
Main benefit: {describe}
Price: {price}

Sections needed: Hero (headline + subhead + CTA), Problem statement, Solution overview, 3 key features with benefits, Social proof section, FAQ (5 questions), Final CTA. Optimize for conversion.

Help me develop a pricing strategy for:

Product/Service: {describe}
Target market: {describe}
Cost to deliver: {describe}
Competitor pricing: {list if known}

Analyze: cost-plus pricing, value-based pricing, competitive pricing, and freemium models. Recommend the best approach with specific price points and tier structures.

Create a 3-month SEO content strategy for: {website/business}.

Niche: {describe}
Current authority: {low/medium/high}

Provide: 12 pillar content topics, 36 supporting articles, keyword clusters for each, internal linking strategy, content calendar, and estimated traffic potential. Prioritize by difficulty and impact.

Create a compelling pitch deck outline for:

Startup: {name}
Problem: {describe}
Solution: {describe}
Stage: {pre-seed/seed/series A}

12 slides: Title, Problem, Solution, Market Size, Business Model, Traction, Competition, Team, Go-to-Market, Financials, Ask, Vision. Include talking points and data suggestions for each slide.

Optimize this SQL query for performance:

{paste SQL query}

Table sizes: {approximate row counts}
Database: {PostgreSQL/MySQL/etc}

Analyze: execution plan issues, missing indexes, join optimization, subquery elimination, and rewrite suggestions. Provide the optimized query with explanations.

Design a KPI dashboard for: {business/department}.

Goals: {list goals}
Data sources: {list}

Provide: Top 8 metrics with calculations, visualization type for each (chart, gauge, number), layout wireframe (text), drill-down hierarchy, alert thresholds, and refresh frequency recommendations.

I need a spreadsheet formula to: {describe what you want to calculate}.

My data layout: {describe columns/rows}
Sample data: {provide examples}
Platform: {Excel/Google Sheets}

Provide the formula, explain each part, show example output, and suggest any helper columns if needed.

Help me analyze this data:

Research question: {describe}
Variables: {list with types}
Sample size: {n}
Data collection method: {describe}

Recommend: appropriate statistical tests, assumptions to check, effect size calculations, visualization approaches, and how to report results. Provide {Python/R} code.

Recommend the best visualization for this data:

Data description: {describe dataset}
Audience: {technical/executive/general}
Key message: {what insight to convey}
Tool: {matplotlib/D3/Tableau/etc}

Provide: chart type recommendation with rationale, color scheme, labeling guidelines, and code to generate it.

Design an ETL pipeline for:

Source: {describe data sources}
Destination: {describe target}
Frequency: {real-time/hourly/daily}
Volume: {approximate}

Provide: architecture diagram (text), transformation logic, error handling strategy, monitoring approach, and code scaffolding in {Python/SQL}.

Help me set up anomaly detection for:

Metric: {describe}
Normal range: {if known}
Data frequency: {per minute/hour/day}
History available: {timeframe}

Recommend: detection method (statistical/ML), threshold calibration, alerting rules, false positive mitigation, and implementation code in Python.

Create a 3-month learning roadmap for: {skill/topic}.

Current level: {beginner/intermediate}
Available time: {hours per week}
Learning style: {reading/video/hands-on}

Provide: weekly goals, specific resources (free), practice projects for each phase, milestones to track progress, and common pitfalls to avoid.
